data.title: Actors Born on February 17
data.meta_description: Famous birthdays in film and TV for the 17th of February. Browse actors, actresses and directors that were born on February 17.
data.text:
Henrietta "Hetty" Beck, Dutch hearing actress (Bouwmeester Award), born in Groningen, Netherlands (d. 1979)

1888 Ronald Arbuthnott Knox, British priest, broadcaster and author (Viaduct Murder), born in Kibworth Leicestershire, England (d. 1957)

Anita Stewart, American silent film actress (South of Hell Mountain), producer, and mystery novelist, born in Brooklyn, NYC (d. 1961)

1895 Edna Park Edwards, American stage and vaudeville actress, born in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania (d. 1967)

Red Barber, American baseball broadcaster (Cincinnati Reds 1934–38, Brooklyn Dodgers 1939–53, NY Yankees 1954–66), born in Columbus, Mississippi (d. 1992)

1908 Staats Cotsworth, American actor (Hamlet, Peyton Place), born in Oak Park, Illinois (d. 1979)

Arthur Hunnicutt, American actor (El Dorado, Big Sky, Apache Uprising), born in Gravelly, Arkansas (d. 1979)

1910 Marc Lawrence [Max Goldsmith], American character actor (Man With Golden Gun), born in New York City (d. 2005)

Arthur Kennedy, American Tony Award-winning stage and screen actor (Death of a Salesman; Fantastic Voyage; Peyton Place; Some Came Running), born in Worcester, Massachusetts (d. 1990)

1914 Per-Jakez Helias, French Breton writer and actor, born in Pouldreuzig, Brittany (d. 1995)

1914 Wayne Morris, American actor and decorated WWII pilot (Paths of Glory, The Bushwackers), born in Los Angeles, California (d. 1959)

Raf Vallone, Italian actor (El Cid, 2 Women, Greek Tycoon), born in Tropea, Italy (d. 2002)

Kathleen Freeman, American actress (Beverly Hillbillies, 3 Ring Circus), born in Chicago, Illinois (d. 2001)

Fritz Behrendt, German-Dutch political cartoonist (Het Parool; De Telegraaf; New York Herald Tribune), born in Berlin, Weimar Republic (d. 2008)

1925 Hal Holbrook, American stage and screen Tony and Emmy award-winning actor (All the President's Men; “Mark Twain Tonight!”), born in Cleveland, Ohio (d. 2021) [1]

Marta Romero, Puerto Rican actress (La Divina Infiel; The Shadow of the Bat), and singer ("Es tarde ya" (It's Too Late Now)), born in Ponce, Puerto Rico (d. 2013)

Dame Patricia Routledge, British stage and screen actress and singer (Keeping Up Appearances; Talking Heads: A Lady of Letters), born in Tranmere, Birkenhead

Alan Bates, British actor (Zorba the Greek; An Unmarried Woman; The Rose), born in Allestree, Derby, England (d. 2003)

1934 Barry Humphries, Australian Tony Award-winning comedian, actor and author known for his stage alter egos (Dame Edna Everage, Sir Les Patterson), born in Melbourne, Victoria (d. 2023) [1]

Christina Pickles, UK-born American actress (St Elsewhere), born in Halifax, England

John Leyton, British actor and singer ("Johnny Remember Me"), born in Frinton-on-Sea, England

Mary Ann Mobley, American model and actress (Miss America-1959, Diff'rent Strokes), Biloxi Mississippi (d. 2014)

Vicente Fernández, Mexican Grammy Award-winning singer, known as "El Rey de la Música Ranchera" (The King of Ranchera Music), actor, and film producer, born in Huentitán El Alto, Jalisco, Mecico (d. 2021)

Brenda Fricker, actress (My Left Foot), born in Dublin, Ireland

1945 Patricia Morrow, American actress (Rita-Peyton Place), born in Los Angeles, California

Andre Dussollier, French actor (3 Men & a Cradle), born in Annecy, France

1946 Zina Bethune, American actress (Nurses, Who's That Knocking at My Door), born in New York City (d. 2012)

Dallas Adams, British actor, painter and writer (Terror From Within)

José José [José Rómulo Sosa Ortiz], Mexican singer and actor, known as 'The Prince of Song', born in Mexico City (d. 2019)

Rene Russo, American model and actress ("Nightcrawler", "Ransom", "Lethal Weapon 3 & 4"), born in Burbank, California

Richard Karn [Wilson], American actor (Home Improvement) and TV game show host (Family Feud), born in Seattle, Washington

Heidi Hagman, American actress (Linda-Archie Bunker's Place), born in New York City

Rowdy Gaines, American swimmer (Olympic gold 100m, 4x100m relay, 4x100m medley 1984; 5 x World C'ship gold 1978, 82) and broadcaster (NBC), born in Winter Haven, Florida

Lou Diamond Phillips, Filipino American actor (La Bamba, Stand & Deliver), born at Subic Bay Naval Station, Philippines

Larry the Cable Guy [Daniel Lawrence Whitney], American comedian (Blue Collar Comedy Tour), born in Pawnee City, Nebraska

Clayton Prince, actor (Hairspray, Reuben-Another World), born in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania

Michael Bay

American film director (Armageddon, Pearl Harbor), born in Los Angeles, California

Chanté Moore, American R&B singer, actress and author (Precious), born in San Francisco, California

Tuesday Knight, American actress, born in Bentwood, California

Dominic Purcell, English-born Australian actor (Prison Break), born in Wallasey, England

Denise Richards, American actress (The World is not Enough), born in Downers Grove, Illinois

1971 Jeremy Edwards, British actor (Holby City), born in London, England

Valeria Mazza, Argentinian model and businesswoman, born in Rosario, Argentina

1972 William Floyd, American football full back (Super Bowl XXIX San Francisco 49ers; Carolina Panthers) and broadcaster (Seminole ISP Sports Network), born in Jacksonville, Florida

Jerry O'Connell, American actor (Scream 2, Andrew-My Secret Identity), born in New York City

Harisu [Lee Kyung-eun], South Korean singer, model and actress, born in Seongnam, Korea

Kelly Carlson, American actress

Bear McCreary, American composer for film, television (Outlander; The Walking Dead: Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.), and video games, born in Fort Lauderdale, Florida

Jason Ritter, American actor and producer (Joan of Arcadia, Gravity Falls, Raising Dion), born in Los Angeles, California

Paris Hilton

American heiress, television personality (The Simple Life), and actress, born in New York City

Joseph Gordon-Levitt, American actor and filmmaker (3rd Rock From the Sun, Inception), born in Los Angeles, California

Jimmy Jacobs, American professional wrestler (Ring of Honor), born in Grand Rapids, Michigan

1984 Kenta Kamakari, Japanese actor and seiyuu, born in Osaka, Japan

Anne Curtis, Filipino actress and commercial model

Bonnie Wright

British actress (Ginny Weasley in "Harry Potter" franchise), born in London, England

1991 Jeremy Allen White, American actor (The Bear), born in Brooklyn, New York

Meaghan Martin, American pop singer (Camp Rock), and actress (10 Things I Hate About You), born in Fallon, Nevada

Sasha Pieterse, South African actress (Pretty Little Liars), born in Johannesburg, South Africa
